data.meta_description: Self potrait by Jamaican British artist, Edna Manley. She was born in Britain in 1900 but relocated to and resided in  Jamaica in 1921 after marrying her cousin and former Prime Minister and current national hero, Norman Manley. She has contributed greatly to the Jamaican Arts and Cultural society and established a college by the name of Edna Manley College of Visual and Performing Arts in 1950. However, in the year 1987 she passed away, but her wonderful masterpieces shall forever live on.
